examples.en: Her book clearly reflects her beliefs.
This action reflects his true beliefs.
His art reflects his cultural identity.
Drive carefully  the wet road reflects.
Wear something white  it reflects the heat.
The pulse reflects the condition of the heart.
The failure reflects badly on the administration.
The mess in his dorm room reflects on the student.
The movie accurately reflects the mood of the time .
His earlier work reflects the influence of his teacher.
His lack of interest in the project reflects badly on him.
The drop in consumer spending reflects concern about the economy.
The senator's uncritical support for the measure reflects his poor judgment.
Art reflects life, or is it the other way around (=is it 'life reflects art')?
The committee reflects the different political currents within the organization.
How much you're paid reflects how important you are to the company you work for.
Some scholars argue that the vexing passage reflects a misreading of the text by an early copyist.
